FeedPackage.Description:
CodeCop is a free to use library that builds on top of JSON to provide a fast unobtrusive way to write method interceptors for your .NET apps.
Interceptor placement is independent from your app's code. It's done on a JSON file which means that at anytime you can add or remove interceptors without code changes or redeploys.
Method interception happens in one or all of these stages, before execution, after execution and it is possible also to override the behavior completely.
CodeCop can intercept your code and also other 3rd party assemblies your app depends on.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Now with Fluent API also.
Visit http://getcodecop.com for full product information.
Read the project's wiki at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/wiki/Home for details on how to get started.
Issues? Please report them at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/issues

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
v3.1 widens CodeCop scope by introducing the Type Creation API: https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/wiki/Type%20Creation%20API
This new API lets you create types at runtime without the need of dynamic compilation or dynamic assemblies. When creating a type you can specify things like inheritance, interfaces, constructor, fields, properties, methods and attributes, in a managed and fluent way, almost resembling F# object expressions.
All types are attached to the mscorlib assembly at runtime.
All other public method interception APIs remain unchanged.
Visit http://getcodecop.com for full product information.
Read the project's wiki at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/wiki/Home for details on how to get started. Issues? Please report them at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/issues

This new API lets you create types at runtime without the need of dynamic compilation or dynamic assemblies. When creating a type you can specify things like inheritance, interfaces, constructor, fields, properties, methods and attributes, in a managed and fluent way, almost resembling F# object expressions.
All types are attached to the mscorlib assembly at runtime.
All other public method interception APIs remain unchanged.
Visit http://getcodecop.com for full product information.
Read the project's wiki at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/wiki/Home for details on how to get started. Issues? Please report them at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/issues
FeedPackage.Summary: The JSON configurable method interception library for .NET
FeedPackage.Tags: CodeCop JSON Method Interception .NET Fluent Free
FeedPackage.Title: CodeCop

FeedPackage.Description:
CodeCop is a free to use library that builds on top of JSON to provide a fast unobtrusive way to write method interceptors for your .NET apps.
Interceptor placement is independent from your app's code. It's done on a JSON file which means that at anytime you can add or remove interceptors without code changes or redeploys.
Method interception happens in one or all of these stages, before execution, after execution and it is possible also to override the behavior completely.
CodeCop can intercept your code and also other 3rd party assemblies your app depends on.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
v3.2 removes external dependency on Json.NET assembly (ilmerged).
Changes to the Process Injection API to allow to load your interceptors from anywhere on disk not only from the target app "bin" folder. Visit http://getcodecop.com for full product information.
Read the project's wiki at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/wiki/Home for details on how to get started. Issues? Please report them at https://bitbucket.org/codecop_team/codecop/issues
